notes: C White was unable to complete his second over (side strain), over completed by NMK Smith. White likely to be replaced for the rest of the tournament.
JA Samarasekera and SF Dukanwala 35 for the 9th wicket, highest 9th wicket partnership in all ODIs at Peshawar. 2nd consecutive match where the best partnership for UAE was for the 9th wicket.
NMK Smith retired ill at 59/1 (after vomiting on the field in the 13th over).

milestones.description: Saleem Raza and Mohammad Aslam's 31-run partnership is UAE's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 13 between Mazhar Hussain and Johanne Samarasekera
Arshad Laeeq has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4) for UAE, going past Azhar Saeed
